  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-44: extend Path 3 (`PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync`) to bind a default Persona via `IScopeResolverService.ResolvePersonaForChatAsync`. The resolved persona content prepends the system prompt so chat-Summarize responses carry the same persona contract as Path 1. Lookup happens at prompt assembly (before LLM call) — does NOT touch streaming. Caching per ADR-014 5-min TTL via the resolver service.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE BFF AI engineer. Knows the Path 1/3 persona binding pattern.</role>

  <goal>
    `ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync` calls `_scopeResolverService.ResolvePersonaForChatAsync(tenantId, cancellationToken)` BEFORE the LLM call and prepends the resolved persona content to the assembled system prompt. Trace log shows persona lookup hit. Unit test asserts the call. Integration test confirms chat-Summarize prompt contains persona content. Streaming unchanged.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-44 + architecture §6.2 (Per-turn prompt assembly): the Path 1 persona binding lives in `PlaybookChatContextProvider.ProvideAsync` calling `ResolvePersonaForChatAsync`. Path 3 currently bypasses persona resolution — specialized playbooks (NDA, Patent, Invoice) thus lack persona context. Adding this binding makes Path 3 consistent with Path 1's contract.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookExecutionEngine.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Scopes/IScopeResolverService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stay within `Services/Ai/` boundary; do not leak resolver into CRUD code.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Persona lookup hits 5-min cache via resolver; verify cache key is tenant-scoped.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Streaming behavior unchanged — persona binding happens at prompt-assembly time only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-44 acceptance — chat-Summarize prompt includes persona content; trace shows persona lookup hit.</constraint>
  </constraints>

