  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `PlaybookChatContextProvider.ProvideAsync` (around line 130-154 per architecture §6.2) to capture the Path 1 persona lookup pattern.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `IScopeResolverService.ResolvePersonaForChatAsync` signature + return contract.</step>
    <step order="3">Read `ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync` (post-task-122 state) to find the prompt-assembly site after `JpsRefResolver`.</step>
    <step order="4">Add persona resolution: call `_scopeResolverService.ResolvePersonaForChatAsync(tenantId, cancellationToken)`; prepend resolved content to the assembled system prompt.</step>
    <step order="5">Confirm `IScopeResolverService` is already injected (likely YES — used by task 122 indirectly via `JpsRefResolver`). If not, add constructor injection.</step>
    <step order="6">Add structured-log entry "persona.resolved" at debug level (deterministic ID only, no content) per ADR-015.</step>
    <step order="7">Add unit test: mock the resolver to return a known persona; assert it appears in the assembled prompt.</step>
    <step order="8">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Must pass.</step>
